Module it.polimi.ingsw.PSP50

Package it.polimi.ingsw.PSP50.network.messages.ToClient

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ChooseGodCard
    Message sent when a Client has to choose a God Card
    DisconnectMessage
    Message sent when a Player has disconnected from the game
    GameStarting
    Message that informs Clients that game is starting
    InitializeWorkers
    Message used to initialize the two workers of the client
    ModelUpdate
    Message that sends a new deep copy of the Model to the Client every time there is a change Original reference of the model is not exposed (defensive programming)
    NameChanged
    Message notifies the Client that his name changed because there is already another player in the game with the same name
    PlayerIdMessage
    Message that set the UI player ID value that the client has on the server
    SelectBlockMessage
    Message that makes a block selection (only for Atlas power)
    SelectBuildMessage
    Message that makes the user select a space where to perform a BUILD action
    SelectMoveMessage
    Message that makes the user select a space where to perform a MOVE action
    SelectWorkerMessage
    Message that makes the user select a worker at the start of his turn
    SetModelCopy
    Message that sets an initial deep copy of the Model inside the client-side view Original reference of the model is not exposed (defensive programming)
    WelcomeMessage
    Message welcomes the client to the game
    WinnerMessage
    WinnerMessage tells every player connected that there is a winner
    WorkerBlocked
    Message sent to the UI when the user selected a worker that he cannot move Used to give the user another chance to the user and not make him lose immediately
    YouLostMessage
    Message sent to a client when he lost before there is a winner: it gives to the client the possibility of staying connected and see how the other players end the game.
